WEBVTT

00:07.708 --> 00:09.777
- FOR ALL OF YOU
WHO WERE TOO FUCKING BUSY,

00:09.777 --> 00:11.712
THIS IS WHAT HAPPENED
LAST WEEK ON SHAMELESS...

00:11.712 --> 00:13.047
- WHAT THE FUCK
YOU LOOKING AT?

00:13.047 --> 00:14.615
- THIS IS MY HOME.

00:14.615 --> 00:16.650
I AM AN IMPORTANT PART
OF THIS FAMILY.

00:16.650 --> 00:19.320
- NO, YOU'RE NOT.
YOU DON'T LIVE HERE ANYMORE.

00:19.320 --> 00:21.389
- CATCH. OPEN IT.

00:21.389 --> 00:23.424
- I SORT OF
HAVE A BOYFRIEND.

00:23.424 --> 00:25.259
- WELL, I SORT OF
HAVE A WIFE.

00:25.259 --> 00:27.995
- SHE'S ALWAYS BEEN A PROBLEM.
- NO!

00:27.995 --> 00:30.331
- I WANT HER TO BE
AN AMERICAN CITIZEN, STEVE.

00:30.331 --> 00:33.734
WHEN IMMIGRATION COMES,
YOU WILL BE HER HUSBAND.

00:33.734 --> 00:36.337
- BETO'S OUT FRONT.
HE FOLLOWS ME WHEREVER I GO.

00:36.337 --> 00:38.305
- HE'S HARMLESS.

00:38.305 --> 00:40.174
- OW! FUCK!

00:40.174 --> 00:41.809
- DADDY'S GOOD WITH BABIES.

00:41.809 --> 00:44.178
- HOWDY, FOLKS.
YOU NEED HELP WITH THAT BABY?

00:44.178 --> 00:46.046
I GOT A PROPOSITION
FOR YOU, SHEILS.

00:46.046 --> 00:48.849
LET ME STAY. YOU'LL GET
EIGHT HOURS OF SLEEP A NIGHT.

00:48.849 --> 00:49.984
I CAN PROMISE YOU THAT.

00:49.984 --> 00:52.987
I KNOW WHAT I'M DOING.

00:52.987 --> 00:55.956
- ARE YOU SUPPOSED
TO GIVE VALIUM TO A BABY?

00:55.956 --> 00:57.992
- I LOST $100
DOING THIS NIGHT.

00:57.992 --> 01:00.661
I WAS TRYING
TO BETTER OUR SITUATION, LIP.

01:00.661 --> 01:02.630
- THE ONLY WAY TO MAKE MONEY
WHEN YOU'RE POOR

01:02.630 --> 01:04.832
IS TO STEAL IT OR SCAM IT.

01:04.832 --> 01:06.634
- I KNOW. I KNOW.
YOU WANT ME TO FIND JESUS.

01:06.634 --> 01:08.269
I ALREADY FOUND HIM.
THANKS.

01:08.269 --> 01:10.471
- I'M LOOKING FOR KEV.

01:10.471 --> 01:12.306
I'M HIS WIFE.

01:19.713 --> 01:22.716
[High Strung's
The Luck You Got]

01:22.716 --> 01:26.554
♪ ♪

01:26.554 --> 01:30.024
- ♪ THINK OF ALL THE LUCK
YOU GOT ♪

01:30.024 --> 01:32.993
♪ KNOW THAT
IT'S NOT FOR NAUGHT ♪

01:32.993 --> 01:36.297
♪ YOU WERE BEAMING
ONCE BEFORE ♪

01:36.297 --> 01:40.501
♪ BUT IT'S NOT LIKE THAT
ANYMORE ♪

01:40.501 --> 01:43.904
♪ WHAT IS THIS DOWN SIDE ♪

01:43.904 --> 01:47.374
♪ THAT YOU SPEAK OF? ♪

01:47.374 --> 01:49.577
♪ WHAT IS THIS FEELING ♪

01:49.577 --> 01:54.215
♪ YOU'RE SO SURE OF? ♪

01:54.215 --> 02:01.055
♪ ♪

02:01.055 --> 02:04.225
♪ ROUND UP THE FRIENDS
YOU GOT ♪

02:04.225 --> 02:07.461
♪ KNOW THAT
THEY'RE NOT FOR NAUGHT ♪

02:07.461 --> 02:10.731
♪ YOU WERE WILLING
ONCE BEFORE ♪

02:10.731 --> 02:15.002
♪ BUT IT'S NOT LIKE THAT
ANYMORE ♪

02:15.002 --> 02:18.372
♪ WHAT IS THIS DOWN SIDE ♪

02:18.372 --> 02:22.076
♪ THAT YOU SPEAK OF? ♪

02:22.076 --> 02:24.044
♪ WHAT IS THIS FEELING ♪

02:24.044 --> 02:28.782
♪ YOU'RE SO SURE OF? ♪

02:28.782 --> 02:31.785
[upbeat music]

02:31.785 --> 02:39.793
♪ ♪

03:15.863 --> 03:17.531
- HEY.

03:17.531 --> 03:19.800
- HEY.

03:19.800 --> 03:21.135
YOU'RE AWAKE.

03:21.135 --> 03:23.237
- NEVER FELL ASLEEP.

03:23.237 --> 03:25.739
- [sighs]
JUST GO TALK TO HIM.

03:25.739 --> 03:27.274
IT'S NOT HIS FAULT
THE CRAZY EX-WIFE

03:27.274 --> 03:28.642
SHOWED UP OUT OF NOWHERE.

03:28.642 --> 03:31.078
- SHE'S NO HIS EX,
SHE'S HIS WIFE.

03:31.078 --> 03:34.515
AND YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN HIS FACE
WHEN HE SAW HER.

03:38.419 --> 03:40.821
THIS HOUSE IS SO QUIET.

03:43.958 --> 03:46.694
- KIDS! BREAKFAST!

03:46.694 --> 03:47.995
- JEEZ, FIONA.

03:47.995 --> 03:49.597
- THIS SHIT
IS ALL IN YOUR HEAD, V.

03:49.597 --> 03:50.931
THIS HOUSE AIN'T QUIET.

03:50.931 --> 03:52.633
AND SHE IS NOT KEV'S WIFE.
YOU ARE.

03:52.633 --> 03:55.202
GO TALK TO HIM.

03:55.202 --> 03:58.305
GET YOUR BOWLS.
GET YOUR PLATES.

03:58.305 --> 04:00.674
[baby crying]

04:00.674 --> 04:02.176
- [groans]

04:02.176 --> 04:03.744
I NEED COFFEE.

04:03.744 --> 04:05.746
- WE'RE OUT OF FILTERS.

04:05.746 --> 04:07.147
- WE CAN USE PAPER TOWELS.

04:07.147 --> 04:09.450
- WE'RE OUT OF PAPER TOWELS.

04:09.450 --> 04:11.485
- DIAPERS WILL WORK.

04:11.485 --> 04:14.188
- YOU HAVE TO GO TO WORK.

04:14.188 --> 04:17.358
- YEAH. CAN WE JUST RESCHEDULE
THE DOCTOR THING?

04:17.358 --> 04:21.362
- NO, THE VACCINE SCHEDULE
IS VERY IMPORTANT.

04:21.362 --> 04:22.796
YOU CAN'T BE LATE.

04:22.796 --> 04:25.466
HOW BUSY CAN A TATTOO PARLOR BE
IN THE MORNING?

04:25.466 --> 04:27.001
- MORNING TO US.

04:27.001 --> 04:29.169
TO SOME PEOPLE, IT'S THE END
OF A LONG NIGHT.

04:29.169 --> 04:31.038
- GOOD MORNING.

04:31.038 --> 04:33.040
NO BREAKFAST?

04:33.040 --> 04:36.243
I HAVEN'T HAD A LOT OF ENERGY
FOR SHOPPING LATELY.

04:36.243 --> 04:38.178
- NANNY FRANK
TO THE RESCUE.

04:38.178 --> 04:40.214
THE HYMSTER AND I WILL GO
ON A LITTLE FIELD TRIP

04:40.214 --> 04:41.715
TO THE GROCERY STORE.

04:41.715 --> 04:44.385
WE JUST NEED SOME CASH,
RIGHT, BUDDY?

04:44.385 --> 04:46.654
- YOU STILL DRUNK, FRANK?

04:46.654 --> 04:50.924
[baby crying]

04:50.924 --> 04:52.426
FINE.

04:52.426 --> 04:54.662
OH, DAMN.
I GOT TO GO.

04:54.662 --> 04:56.830
I'LL GRAB COFFEE
ON THE WAY TO WORK.

04:59.500 --> 05:00.868
BOO-DA-LOO-BOOP.

05:00.868 --> 05:04.071
[baby crying]

05:14.048 --> 05:16.216
[crying stops]

05:16.216 --> 05:17.418
- I'M AWAKE!

05:17.418 --> 05:18.919
[baby crying]
OH.

05:18.919 --> 05:21.221
- GO CATCH SOME "Z"s, SHEILS.

05:21.221 --> 05:24.191
I GOT THE LITTLE GUY.
- I CAN'T.

05:24.191 --> 05:26.226
HYMIE HAS HIS FIRST
"WELL BABY" APPOINTMENT TODAY

05:26.226 --> 05:28.062
AT THE PEDIATRICIAN.

05:28.062 --> 05:30.364
- DOCTOR REQUIRE
SOME KIND OF CO-PAY

05:30.364 --> 05:32.499
FOR THIS UNNECESSARY VISIT?

05:32.499 --> 05:35.235
- OH, OF COURSE HE DOES.

05:35.235 --> 05:38.539
- DOCTORS ARE THIEVES,
LITTLE HYMSTER.

05:38.539 --> 05:41.709
THEY JUST HAVE DEGREES
TO KEEP THEM OUT OF JAIL.

05:41.709 --> 05:43.277
GO ON.
I'LL TAKE HIM.

05:43.277 --> 05:45.612
- [gasps]
YOU WILL?

05:45.612 --> 05:47.214
- YEAH.
- FRANK!

05:47.214 --> 05:50.617
OH, FRANK, BLESS YOU.
BLESS YOU.

05:50.617 --> 05:52.219
[baby crying]
BLESS YOU.

05:52.219 --> 05:53.587
OH. OKAY.

05:53.587 --> 05:55.289
HERE. HERE.
- OKAY.

05:55.289 --> 05:56.990
- HERE YOU GO.
- THAT'LL DO IT.

05:56.990 --> 05:58.559
OOH, LOOK AT THAT.

05:58.559 --> 06:01.395
- OH, WAIT.
DON'T YOU NEED THE ADDRESS?

06:12.573 --> 06:16.043
- WHERE IS SHE?
- SHE'S STILL SLEEPING.

06:16.043 --> 06:18.879
- SHE DID NOT JUST SHOW UP HERE
BECAUSE HER CAR BROKE DOWN.

06:18.879 --> 06:21.115
- WHAT DO YOU THINK, V,
SHE BROKE IT ON PURPOSE?

06:21.115 --> 06:22.916
- I THINK SHE BROKE YOU
ON PURPOSE.

06:22.916 --> 06:24.551
SHE BROKE YOU.

06:24.551 --> 06:26.120
AND I PUT YOU BACK TOGETHER.

06:26.120 --> 06:27.921
AND NOW SHE'S HERE
TO TAKE BACK WHAT I FIXED.

06:27.921 --> 06:29.990
- V, LOOK.
LOOK AT THIS.

06:29.990 --> 06:32.626
DIVORCE PAPERS--
I GOT THEM OFF THE INTERNET.

06:32.626 --> 06:34.228
THIS IS MY CHANCE
TO GET HER TO SIGN IT,

06:34.228 --> 06:35.796
TO MAKE IT OFFICIAL.

06:35.796 --> 06:37.731
- WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST SAY THAT
LAST NIGHT?

06:37.731 --> 06:39.767
- BECAUSE YOU WERE YELLING
SOME SHIT ABOUT MY FACE,

06:39.767 --> 06:41.769
AND THEN YOU DITCHED
AND SLEPT OVER AT FIONA'S.

06:41.769 --> 06:44.004
- WELL, I WAS RIGHT
ABOUT YOUR FACE.

06:44.004 --> 06:45.839
- [yawns]

06:48.008 --> 06:49.676
GOOD MORNING.

06:49.676 --> 06:51.311
- HEY.

06:51.311 --> 06:52.613
I MADE YOU SOME COFFEE--

06:52.613 --> 06:53.781
SUPER STRONG,
LIKE YOU LIKE IT.

06:53.781 --> 06:56.683
- YAY, KEVY-CAF, MY FAVE.

06:56.683 --> 06:58.352
- "KEVY-CAF"?

06:58.352 --> 07:01.155
- DECAF, FULL-CAF, KEVY-CAF--

07:01.155 --> 07:03.090
FOR WHEN YOU NEED
A REAL KICK IN THE ASS.

07:03.090 --> 07:05.793
- CAN I WATCH SOME TV?
- YEAH.

07:05.793 --> 07:06.994
- [gags]

07:06.994 --> 07:08.428
- IT'S HOW SHE LIKES IT.

07:08.428 --> 07:09.930
- MMM.

07:09.930 --> 07:12.099
YOUR BED IS SO COMFY.
I SLEPT LIKE A BABY.

07:12.099 --> 07:13.801
- YOU SLEPT IN OUR BED?

07:13.801 --> 07:15.102
- I STAYED
IN THE GUEST ROOM.

07:15.102 --> 07:16.603
- [sighs]
GOD.

07:16.603 --> 07:18.172
I HAVEN'T SMELLED THAT SMELL
IN SO LONG.

07:18.172 --> 07:19.540
- WHAT SMELL?

07:19.540 --> 07:21.975
- HIS COLOGNE...
ON THE PILLOW.

07:21.975 --> 07:23.443
- ENGLISH LEATHER,
LIKE...

07:23.443 --> 07:25.512
both: OLD MAN CARLYLE
USED TO WEAR.

07:25.512 --> 07:26.680
- [giggles]

07:26.680 --> 07:27.781
- "OLD MAN CARLYLE"?

07:27.781 --> 07:29.716
- FOSTER HOME WHERE WE MET.

07:29.716 --> 07:32.019
HE WAS THE BEST FAKE DAD
WE EVER HEAD.

07:32.019 --> 07:33.654
YOU KNOW
JUNIOR'S GOING TO PRISON?

07:33.654 --> 07:36.156
TAX EVASION.
- JUNIOR CARLYLE, NO SHIT?

07:36.156 --> 07:38.358
- NO SHIT.
- NO SHIT?

07:42.729 --> 07:45.399
- SIX FROZEN OJs
FOR THE PRICE OF FIVE.

07:45.399 --> 07:46.834
20% OFF MAC AND CHEESE,

07:46.834 --> 07:48.502
AND I HAVE FOUR OF THESE.

07:48.502 --> 07:50.204
- ONLY ONE COUPON
PER CUSTOMER.

07:50.204 --> 07:51.839
- IT DOESN'T SAY THAT.
- IT DOESN'T HAVE TO.

07:51.839 --> 07:52.906
IT'S IMPLIED.
- HEY, TINA.

07:52.906 --> 07:54.441
IT'S TIME FOR YOUR BREAK.

07:54.441 --> 07:56.510
WHY DON'T YOU HAVE KIM
TAKE OVER YOUR STATION?

07:56.510 --> 07:58.512
- OH, MY GOD.

07:58.512 --> 08:00.581
IS THAT SNOT?
- SORRY--

08:00.581 --> 08:01.849
KIDS, SUMMER COLDS.

08:01.849 --> 08:04.117
- I HAVE FOUR
MAC AND CHEESE COUPONS--

08:04.117 --> 08:06.553
- I TOLD YOU, ONE PER CUSTOMER.
- HEY, WATCH YOUR TONE.

08:06.553 --> 08:07.855
- I'LL WATCH MY TONE
WHEN YOU TEACH YOUR KIDS

08:07.855 --> 08:09.156
HOW TO USE A KLEENEX.
- EXCUSE ME?

08:09.156 --> 08:10.624
- I HAVE FOUR COUPONS!

08:10.624 --> 08:12.125
I DUG THROUGH
THE NEIGHBOR'S TRASH

08:12.125 --> 08:14.628
TO GET THEM!
- TINA, BREAK TIME!

08:14.628 --> 08:16.330
LET'S GO.
- YOU KNOW WHAT? FINE!

08:16.330 --> 08:18.999
TAKE IT. TAKE ALL OF IT!
TAKE IT FOR FREE!

08:18.999 --> 08:20.033
I DON'T GIVE A SHIT!

08:20.033 --> 08:21.034
DO YOU HEAR ME, BOBBY?

08:21.034 --> 08:22.369
I DON'T GIVE A SHIT!

08:22.369 --> 08:23.770
TAKE YOUR OWN GODDAMN BREAK!

08:23.770 --> 08:25.172
AND YOU CAN KEEP
MY LAST PAYCHECK.

08:25.172 --> 08:26.673
I WON'T BE COMING BACK.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.208
KEEP TAKING THIS SHIT
IF YOU WANT TO.

08:28.208 --> 08:30.410
BUT I'M OUT, BITCHES.
OUT!

08:30.410 --> 08:32.079
- WHY DON'T WE JUST TALK HERE
FOR A SECOND, TINA.

08:32.079 --> 08:35.549
OKAY.

08:35.549 --> 08:38.285
- MAYBE I SHOULDN'T HAVE PUSHED
SO HARD ON THE COUPON THING.

08:38.285 --> 08:40.687
- JUST, UH, STAY HERE
AND BAG THE GROCERIES.

08:40.687 --> 08:42.289
- WE DIDN'T PAY.

08:42.289 --> 08:44.591
- SHE SAID WE COULD HAVE 'EM.

08:44.591 --> 08:46.226
- EXCUSE ME.

08:46.226 --> 08:47.694
EXCUSE ME.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.229
ARE YOU THE MANAGER?

08:49.229 --> 08:50.764
- UH, YES.
I'M SO SORRY

08:50.764 --> 08:52.199
YOU HAD TO HEAR
THAT KIND OF LANGUAGE

08:52.199 --> 08:53.767
WITH YOUR CHILDREN PRESENT,
MA'AM.

08:53.767 --> 08:55.602
IF YOU'D, UH, FOLLOW ME BACK
TO MY OFFICE,

08:55.602 --> 08:57.304
I'D BE HAPPY TO GIVE YOU
A COUPON FOR A FREE HAM.

08:57.304 --> 08:58.839
- THAT'D BE GREAT.

08:58.839 --> 09:00.741
BUT IT SEEMS LIKE
SHE KIND OF QUIT BACK THERE,

09:00.741 --> 09:03.877
SO I WAS THINKING THERE
MIGHT BE A JOB OPENING.

09:03.877 --> 09:05.913
- HMM.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

09:05.913 --> 09:07.581
- FIONA GALLAGHER.

09:07.581 --> 09:09.016
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

09:09.016 --> 09:11.418
WHY DON'T YOU FOLLOW ME,
FIONA GALLAGHER?

09:12.886 --> 09:15.522
SO, RIGHT PLACE,
RIGHT TIME, HUH?

09:15.522 --> 09:17.224
- HOPE SO.

09:17.224 --> 09:19.026
I'M RESPONSIBLE
AND A REALLY HARD WORKER.

09:19.026 --> 09:22.362
- YOU EVER WORK AS A CASHIER?
- SURE, ABSOLUTELY.

09:22.362 --> 09:25.766
- SO, TELL ME, FIONA,

09:25.766 --> 09:28.035
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT DELI MEATS?

09:28.035 --> 09:30.337
- DELI MEATS?

09:30.337 --> 09:32.339
I'M NOT BIG ON OLIVE LOAF--

09:32.339 --> 09:34.207
BARFED IT UP ONCE
WHEN I WAS A KID.

09:34.207 --> 09:36.009
BUT MOSTLY I LIKE 'EM.
- GOOD.

09:36.009 --> 09:37.744
THAT'S GOOD.

09:37.744 --> 09:40.480
I ASK, BECAUSE IF YOU'RE GONNA
BE WORKING HERE,

09:40.480 --> 09:44.017
I GOT TO SEE
HOW YOU HANDLE THE MEAT.

09:44.017 --> 09:46.119
WE SELL FRANKS AND BEANS TOO.

09:46.119 --> 09:49.856
WE SELL HOT DOGS,
CORN DOGS,

09:49.856 --> 09:53.760
THREE BEAN SALAD,
CREAM CHEESE.

09:53.760 --> 09:55.162
- [chuckles]
WOW.

09:55.162 --> 09:56.763
YOU'RE SAYING
THAT IF BLOW YOU,

09:56.763 --> 09:58.165
I CAN HAVE A JOB?

09:58.165 --> 10:00.667
- NO.
I WOULD NEVER SAY THAT.

10:00.667 --> 10:02.669
THAT WOULD BE INAPPROPRIATE
AND ILLEGAL.

10:02.669 --> 10:04.671
IF YOU WANTED
TO BLOW ME,

10:04.671 --> 10:07.641
WELL, YOU'D HAVE TO BE
A CONSENTING ADULT.

10:09.743 --> 10:11.578
- GOOD MORNING, FRANK.
WHO'S YOUR HANDSOME FRIEND?

10:11.578 --> 10:13.547
- [chuckles]
YOU HEAR THAT, HYMIE?

10:13.547 --> 10:16.383
THAT'S KATE.
KATE'S GOT GOOD TASTE.

10:16.383 --> 10:19.419
GIVE ME A SHOT OF J.B.,
A PICKLED EGG,

10:19.419 --> 10:22.356
AND A THUMBTACK.

10:22.356 --> 10:25.492
- A THUMBTACK?

10:25.492 --> 10:26.994
- AND A BAND-AID.

10:26.994 --> 10:30.530
[baby crying]

10:32.332 --> 10:36.136
[trilling lips]

10:36.136 --> 10:38.038
THERE YOU GO AND--

10:38.038 --> 10:39.740
MUMPS BE GONE.
[baby crying]

10:39.740 --> 10:41.308
OH, YES, YES, YES, YES.

10:41.308 --> 10:42.743
YES, YES, YES, YES, YES.

10:42.743 --> 10:44.778
YEAH, IT'S ALL OVER,
LITTLE BUDDY.

10:44.778 --> 10:47.080
THERE YOU GO.
THERE YOU GO.

10:47.080 --> 10:49.082
I'M GONNA NEED
ANOTHER ONE OF THESE.

10:49.082 --> 10:52.486
- UM, I THINK I'M--
YEAH.

10:52.486 --> 10:55.088
I'M CALLING THE POLICE
AND REPORTING CHILD ABUSE.

10:55.088 --> 10:56.456
- [trills lips]

10:56.456 --> 10:58.558
AIDS DIDN'T COME
FROM THE HOMOS, KATE.

10:58.558 --> 11:00.594
THE GAYS MAY HAVE HELPED
TO SPREAD IT,

11:00.594 --> 11:02.529
WITH THEIR BLOODY
ANAL PASSIONS,

11:02.529 --> 11:05.332
BUT IT ORIGINATED
IN VACCINES

11:05.332 --> 11:07.401
MADE FROM THE BLOOD
OF AFRICAN MONKEYS.

11:07.401 --> 11:11.138
INTERESTINGLY ENOUGH,
HETEROSEXUAL MONKEYS.

11:11.138 --> 11:13.874
- IT WAS HOMOS, FRANK.
- [chuckles]

11:13.874 --> 11:15.275
- HE NEEDS HIS SHOTS, FRANK.

11:15.275 --> 11:17.144
- JESUS CHRIST, KATE.

11:17.144 --> 11:18.812
THE KID'S ALREADY A HALF-WIT.

11:18.812 --> 11:20.380
YOU WANT TO GIVE HIM
AUTISM TOO?

11:20.380 --> 11:21.815
NOW CLOSE YOUR MOUTH

11:21.815 --> 11:23.617
BEFORE SOMEONE CONSIDERS IT
AN INVITATION,

11:23.617 --> 11:26.086
AND POUR ME A GODDAMN DRINK.

11:26.086 --> 11:27.788
- THE STARS CAME OUT

11:27.788 --> 11:29.723
FOR THE WISHING LANE FOUNDATION
LAST NIGHT.

11:29.723 --> 11:32.325
ADAM FOSTER, TEN YEARS OLD,
AND LIVING

11:32.325 --> 11:35.562
WITH A RARE FORM LEUKEMIA,
HAD ONLY ONE WISH--

11:35.562 --> 11:37.464
TO MEET HIS HEROES,
THE BULLS.

11:37.464 --> 11:39.900
THEY DID BETTER THAN THAT,
GIVING HIM COURTSIDE SEATS

11:39.900 --> 11:41.868
AND A BALL
SIGNED BY THE ENTIRE TEAM.

11:41.868 --> 11:43.970
- HOLY SHIT.
THE WHOLE TEAM?

11:43.970 --> 11:45.605
WHAT DO YOU THINK
THAT'D GO FOR ON EBAY?

11:45.605 --> 11:48.775
- COUPLE GRAND, AT LEAST.

11:48.775 --> 11:50.310
- THAT KID'S
JUST GOT CANCER.

11:50.310 --> 11:51.711
HYMIE'S MENTALLY DEFICIENT.

11:51.711 --> 11:53.713
THAT'S A PERMANENT CONDITION.

11:53.713 --> 11:57.017
- YOU SHOULD KNOW, FRANK.
- [laughs]

11:57.017 --> 11:59.119
- [trills lips]

12:02.589 --> 12:04.558
- THAT WOULD BE
AN AWESOME JOB!

12:04.558 --> 12:06.326
DISCOUNTS ON GROCERIES--

12:06.326 --> 12:08.428
THAT COULD REALLY HELP
WITH SUMMER DAY CARE COSTS.

12:08.428 --> 12:10.664
- I'M NOT GETTING THAT JOB.

12:10.664 --> 12:14.134
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN, SO LET'S
JUST DROP IT, OKAY, DEBS?

12:21.641 --> 12:24.111
DEBS?

12:29.049 --> 12:31.852
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

12:31.852 --> 12:34.955
GET OUT OF HERE,
YOU PIECE OF SHIT!

12:34.955 --> 12:37.657
YOU BETTER RUN,
YOU SICK BASTARD!

12:37.657 --> 12:40.227
[hard rock music]

12:40.227 --> 12:46.299
♪ ♪

